        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Unit tests should be independent. Each test should fully initialize its environment. \n\nUse of classes such as Zend_Auth and Zend_Registry [other examples ???] currently requires the user to use methods such as _unsetInstance() and clearIdentity() in test tearDowns to maintain independence. \n\nThis leads to some repetition and (perhaps) could be handled by Zend_Test itself. \n\n(One reservation I have is that such a feature might enforce a particular way of handling such objects and so would need to be well thought through and documented.) "
        },
