        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28335",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I see some merit in this idea, but it has always been the responsibility of the test writer to guarantee test isolation. It seems that if Zend_Test were to do it for you, there would have to be pretty strict conventions on where stuff is put, like everything goes in the registry. This isn't really the ZF way.\nMatthew, can you evaluate and close the issue if you agree?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-20T16:58:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-20T16:58:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28346",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=carlton",
                        "name": "carlton",
                        "displayName": "Carlton Gibson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Perhaps all is needed here is a _guide_ to the components that are likely to need resetting and an example of how it's done. (Rather than more code per se.) This could be used as a checklist\/cheatsheet when writing tests. \n\nIf this is the way to go, I would be happy to write up the guide if, say, Matthew could 1) check that the list of components I came up with was complete (enough) and 2) cast an editorial eye over the final product. Hopefully this would be less work than Matthew just writing it himself :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=carlton",
                        "name": "carlton",
                        "displayName": "Carlton Gibson",
